  <graph edgedefault="undirected">
    <node id="Reentrancy Attack">
      <data key="d0">Reentrancy Attack</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Reentrancy Attack, also known as recursive call attack, involves a malicious contract calling back into the calling contract before the first invocation of the function is finished, potentially causing undesirable interactions.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fef8945d8c2c009caf505df5783cfa41</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-107.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004444</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CWE-841">
      <data key="d0">CWE-841</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">CWE-841 refers to Improper Enforcement of Behavioral Workflow, highlighting a weakness in managing control flow in software.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fef8945d8c2c009caf505df5783cfa41</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-107.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004444</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Checks-Effects-Interactions Pattern">
      <data key="d0">Checks-Effects-Interactions Pattern</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Checks-Effects-Interactions Pattern is a best practice in smart contract development to prevent reentrancy attacks by ensuring all internal state changes occur before external calls.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fef8945d8c2c009caf505df5783cfa41</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-107.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004444</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ReentrancyGuard">
      <data key="d0">ReentrancyGuard</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">ReentrancyGuard, like OpenZeppelin's ReentrancyGuard, is a reentrancy lock used to prevent reentrancy vulnerabilities in smart contracts.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fef8945d8c2c009caf505df5783cfa41</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-107.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004444</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ModifierEntrancy">
      <data key="d0">ModifierEntrancy</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">ModifierEntrancy is a smart contract that demonstrates a reentrancy vulnerability in its original form (modifier_reentrancy.sol) and a fix in a later version (modifier_reentrancy_fixed.sol).</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fef8945d8c2c009caf505df5783cfa41</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-107.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004444</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Bank">
      <data key="d0">Bank</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Bank is a smart contract used in conjunction with ModifierEntrancy to simulate a scenario where reentrancy vulnerabilities can occur.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fef8945d8c2c009caf505df5783cfa41</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-107.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004444</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Nu Token">
      <data key="d0">Nu Token</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Nu Token is a token referenced within the smart contracts used to demonstrate reentrancy vulnerabilities.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fef8945d8c2c009caf505df5783cfa41</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-107.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004444</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SimpleDAO">
      <data key="d0">SimpleDAO</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">SimpleDAO is a smart contract vulnerable to reentrancy attacks, as demonstrated in simple_dao.sol, and a fixed version, as shown in simple_dao_fixed.sol.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fef8945d8c2c009caf505df5783cfa41</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-107.md</data>
