    <node id="Version 0.4.13">
      <data key="d0">Version 0.4.13</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Version 0.4.13 is an outdated version of the Solidity compiler that has known bugs and vulnerabilities.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b61125c1cec927c55744ac05237483a7</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-102.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004803</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Version 0.8.21">
      <data key="d0">Version 0.8.21</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Version 0.8.21 is a more recent version of the Solidity compiler (as of August 2023), with numerous bug fixes compared to version 0.4.13.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b61125c1cec927c55744ac05237483a7</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-102.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004803</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OutdatedCompilerVersion Contract">
      <data key="d0">OutdatedCompilerVersion Contract</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">The contract shows the pragma to use solidity version 0.4.13</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b61125c1cec927c55744ac05237483a7</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-102.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004803</data>
    </node>
    <node id="M_required">
      <data key="d0">M_required</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">M_required represents the number of confirmations required for an operation to be executed.&lt;SEP&gt;M_required is a public uint that represents the number of owners required to confirm an operation before it is executed.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fddd054638bdb39f44cdac4d32292bf7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a1ab0c06a8f5a5e95314dbbe5a5ff77</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004948</data>
    </node>
    <node id="M_numOwners">
      <data key="d0">M_numOwners</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">M_numOwners represents the number of owners in the multi-signature wallet contract.&lt;SEP&gt;M_numOwners is a public uint that represents the number of owners.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fddd054638bdb39f44cdac4d32292bf7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a1ab0c06a8f5a5e95314dbbe5a5ff77</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004948</data>
    </node>
    <node id="M_dailyLimit">
      <data key="d0">M_dailyLimit</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">M_dailyLimit represents the daily limit.&lt;SEP&gt;M_dailyLimit is a public uint representing the daily limit.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fddd054638bdb39f44cdac4d32292bf7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a1ab0c06a8f5a5e95314dbbe5a5ff77</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004948</data>
    </node>
    <node id="M_spentToday">
      <data key="d0">M_spentToday</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">M_spentToday is a public uint representing the amount spent today.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fddd054638bdb39f44cdac4d32292bf7</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004948</data>
    </node>
    <node id="M_lastDay">
      <data key="d0">M_lastDay</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">M_lastDay represents last day&lt;SEP&gt;M_lastDay is a public uint representing the last day.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fddd054638bdb39f44cdac4d32292bf7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a1ab0c06a8f5a5e95314dbbe5a5ff77</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004948</data>
    </node>
    <node id="M_owners">
      <data key="d0">M_owners</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">M_owners is an array storing the addresses of the owners of the multi-signature wallet.&lt;SEP&gt;M_owners is a uint array of size 256 that stores the list of owners.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fddd054638bdb39f44cdac4d32292bf7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a1ab0c06a8f5a5e95314dbbe5a5ff77</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004948</data>
    </node>
    <node id="C_maxOwners">
      <data key="d0">C_maxOwners</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">C_maxOwners represents the maximum number of owners allowed in the multi-signature wallet.&lt;SEP&gt;C_maxOwners is a constant uint equal to 250, representing the maximum number of owners.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fddd054638bdb39f44cdac4d32292bf7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a1ab0c06a8f5a5e95314dbbe5a5ff77</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004948</data>
    </node>
    <node id="M_ownerIndex">
      <data key="d0">M_ownerIndex</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">M_ownerIndex is a mapping that stores the index of each owner's address in the m_owners array.&lt;SEP&gt;M_ownerIndex is a mapping from uint to uint that serves as an index on the list of owners, allowing reverse lookup.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fddd054638bdb39f44cdac4d32292bf7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a1ab0c06a8f5a5e95314dbbe5a5ff77</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004948</data>
    </node>
    <node id="M_pending">
      <data key="d0">M_pending</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">M_pending is a mapping from bytes32 to PendingState, representing the ongoing operations.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fddd054638bdb39f44cdac4d32292bf7</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004980</data>
    </node>
    <node id="M_pendingIndex">
      <data key="d0">M_pendingIndex</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">M_pendingIndex is an array of bytes32 representing the index of pending operations.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fddd054638bdb39f44cdac4d32292bf7</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004980</data>
    </node>
    <node id="M_txs">
      <data key="d0">M_txs</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">M_txs is a mapping from bytes32 to Transaction, representing the pending transactions.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fddd054638bdb39f44cdac4d32292bf7</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004980</data>
    </node>
    <node id="WalletLibrary">
      <data key="d0">WalletLibrary</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">WalletLibrary is a Solidity contract implementing multi-signature wallet functionality.&lt;SEP&gt;The WalletLibrary has a constant address.&lt;SEP&gt;WalletLibrary is a contract with a constant address 0xcafecafecafecafecafecafecafecafecafecafe.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fddd054638bdb39f44cdac4d32292bf7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd0f37ab9e07be52654d940b05a8abd9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-325e7cb597212ca943c4948538630c1f</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004980</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SimpleSuicide">
      <data key="d0">SimpleSuicide</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">SimpleSuicide is a contract with a function to selfdestruct.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fddd054638bdb39f44cdac4d32292bf7</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004980</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SuicideMultiTxFeasible">
      <data key="d0">SuicideMultiTxFeasible</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">SuicideMultiTxFeasible is a contract that can self-destruct if initialized is not zero.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fddd054638bdb39f44cdac4d32292bf7</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004980</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SuicideMultiTxInfeasible">
      <data key="d0">SuicideMultiTxInfeasible</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">SuicideMultiTxInfeasible is a contract that can self-destruct if initialized is not equal to 2.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fddd054638bdb39f44cdac4d32292bf7</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763004980</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SELFDESTRUCT Instruction">
      <data key="d0">SELFDESTRUCT Instruction</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The SELFDESTRUCT instruction allows a contract to destroy itself, potentially leading to vulnerabilities if not properly protected.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bd0f37ab9e07be52654d940b05a8abd9</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763005006</data>
    </node>
    <node id="CWE-284">
      <data key="d0">CWE-284</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">CWE-284 refers to Improper Access Control, a security weakness that can lead to unauthorized actions.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bd0f37ab9e07be52654d940b05a8abd9</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763005006</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EthTrust Security Levels">
      <data key="d0">EthTrust Security Levels</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">EthTrust Security Levels are standards for Ethereum contract security.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bd0f37ab9e07be52654d940b05a8abd9</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763005006</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Protect Self-destruction">
      <data key="d0">Protect Self-destruction</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Protect Self-destruction is an EthTrust Security Level requirement that focuses on securing the self-destruct functionality of a contract.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bd0f37ab9e07be52654d940b05a8abd9</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763005006</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Enforce Least Privilege">
      <data key="d0">Enforce Least Privilege</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Enforce Least Privilege is an EthTrust Security Level requirement that emphasizes limiting access rights to the minimum necessary.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bd0f37ab9e07be52654d940b05a8abd9</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763005006</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Parity &quot;I accidentally killed it&quot; Bug">
      <data key="d0">Parity "I accidentally killed it" Bug</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">The Parity "I accidentally killed it" bug is a past incident where a vulnerability related to self-destruction resulted in significant consequences.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bd0f37ab9e07be52654d940b05a8abd9</data>
      <data key="d4">SWC-106.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1763005006</data>
    </node>
    <node id="WalletLibrary.sol">
      <data key="d0">WalletLibrary.sol</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">WalletLibrary.sol is a sample Solidity smart contract that implements a multi-signature wallet.</data>
